Esh (Êƒ) is a programming friendly shell with a syntax suitable for both
executing shell tasks and writing functions.

Examples:

$ 1+2
3
$ ls
README esh.rb
$ x = "."
$ ls #{x}
README esh.rb
$ ls | _.split("\n").size
2
$ [1,2,3]
[1, 2, 3]
$ ['a', 'b', 'c'].join("\n")
"a\nb\nc"
$ puts ['a', 'b', 'c'].join("\n")
a
b
c
$ ['a', 'b', 'c'].join("\n") | wc
       2       3       5
$ jobs
[]
$ ping google.com
